<br>
The character builder is top notch, with the ability to choose your alignment, race (and a sub-race that you can name yourself), class, &quot;packages&quot; (skills that can be customised for those who like making their own style of class), appearance (right down to the exact colour of skin, tattoos etc) and my personal favourite, the voice style of your character (I personally love the Psychotic Maniac voice! &quot;Die!, Die!!, DIE!!!, DIEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEE!!!!!!!&quot;)<br>
<br>
The single player storyline is quite good too, with some twists and turns, and the voice acting is quite good too, especially some of the stuff that Tomi Undergallows comes out with.<br>
<br>
You can hire henchmen, do quests or even go on a massacre and wipe an entire town out if you feel like it.<br>
<br>
The expecially interesting part is the fact that you can create your own single and multiplayer storylines using the editor. I've been tinkering with it but so far it's been quite difficult to get used to. Some people are creating an Everquest Module for the game, several zones have been released such as EC and Befallen with mobs and custom loot exactly where they should be, so it seems like a winner.<br>
<br>
I'd recommend it to anyone. <p><HTML><BODY>
